> Spinach always gives your plate needs a pop of color—but this leafy green has so much more to offer! That's why our chefs finally gave spinach the starring role it deserves. Sautéed shallot and spinach are mixed with melty Italian cheese, then stuffed inside chicken that's topped with a golden panko crust. A garlicky sauce, caprese salad, and toasted ciabatta ties it all together. Show-stopping spinach? You saw it here first, folks!

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and thinly slice @shallot{1}(peeled and thinly sliced).

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add half the shallot (you'll use the rest later) and cook, stirring occasionally, until softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add half the @spinach{5%oz} (you'll use the rest later) and cook, stirring often, until just wilted, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #medium bowl{} and immediately stir in @Italian cheese blend{1/2%cup} and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Wipe out pan.

Reserve 1/2 tsp @Italian seasoning{1%tbsp} for step 5. Place @butter{2%tbsp} in a small, microwave-safe #bowl{}. Microwave until melted, ~{1%minute}.

In a second medium bowl, combine @panko breadcrumbs{1/2%cup}, remaining Italian seasoning, melted butter, @salt{1/2%tsp}, and @pepper{}. Transfer panko mixture to a shallow #dish{}. Wipe out bowl used for butter.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%oz} dry with paper towels; place between 2 large pieces of #plastic wrap{}. Pound with a #mallet{} or #rolling pin{} until chicken is about 1/4 inch thick. Remove and discard top layer of plastic wrap. Season chicken all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Keeping chicken on plastic wrap, add spinach filling to the bottom third of each cutlet. Tightly roll up chicken over filling, starting with filled sides and removing plastic wrap as you go.

Brush stuffed chicken all over with @sour cream{1.5%tbsp} (including the open ends). Working one piece at a time, press chicken into panko mixture to coat on all sides.

Place stuffed chicken on a lightly oiled #baking sheet{}. Roast on top rack until cooked through, about ~{18%minutes}.

Set oven to broil and roast until golden brown, ~{1-3%minutes} more.

> Watch closely to avoid burning.

== Caprese Salad ==

Halve @grape tomatoes{4%oz} lengthwise. Cut @fresh mozzarella{4%oz} into 1/2-inch cubes.

In a large #bowl{}, toss together tomatoes, remaining shallot, a drizzle of @olive oil{}, and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Set aside.

== Toasted Basil Ciabatta ==

Heat a drizzle of olive oil in pan used for spinach over medium heat. Stir in reserved Italian seasoning, then immediately add @ciabatta bread{1}(halved lengthwise), cut sides down, to pan. Press down lightly and cook until cut sides are golden, ~{3-6%minutes}.

Transfer to a #cutting board{}; sprinkle with a pinch of salt and pepper and drizzle with @basil oil{5%tsp} to taste. Halve on a diagonal.

== Garlic Sauce ==

In bowl used for butter, whisk together @chicken demi-glace{1}, @garlic powder{1%tsp}, and @water{2%tsp} until combined.

Microwave until warmed through, ~{30-45%seconds}. Stir in @butter{1%tbsp} until melted and combined.

Reheat sauce in microwave for ~{15%seconds} if needed.

== Assembly ==

To bowl with tomatoes and shallot, add @honey Dijon dressing{1.5%tbsp}, mozzarella, and remaining spinach; toss to combine. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

Divide chicken, salad, and ciabatta between plates. Top chicken with sauce and serve.